# Riverpod

`ProviderScope` wraps the app in `main.dart`. `riverpod_lint` is enabled — follow analyzer hints.

## Provider layout

- `localStorageProvider` / `isarProvider` — async open, override in tests
- `*RepositoryProvider` — binds interface → data implementation
- `*ServiceProvider` — business API consumed by UI
- Screen-specific: `Notifier` / `AsyncNotifier` for session state (e.g. active workout sets)

## Rules

- Widgets `ref.watch` for rebuild; `ref.read` in callbacks / one-shot actions
- Do not pass `Isar` or repositories deep into widget trees — use providers
- `AsyncValue` for load/save; surface errors with `SelectableText.rich` or snackbar, not silent failure
- Keep `StatelessWidget` + providers default; `StatefulWidget` only for ephemeral UI (text controllers, animations)

## UI ↔ domain

Presentation calls service methods (`logWeight`, `addFoodFromPreset`, `completeSet`), never writes Isar directly.

Invalidate or refresh providers after mutations that affect dashboard aggregates (`DailyLog` for today).

## Avoid

- `setState` for data that other screens need
- Global singletons outside Riverpod
- `ChangeNotifier` unless integrating a legacy API
